/CHAPTER The Treelord Galar Nut CHAPTER/

Galar Nut is a /ARTICLEREF /REFNAME ./SarduniElves.html REFNAME/  /REFTEXT sarduni REFTEXT/ ARTICLEREF/  /ARTICLEREF /REFNAME ./TreeLord.html REFNAME/  /REFTEXT TreeLord REFTEXT/ ARTICLEREF/  with an ancestral claim in the /ARTICLEREF /REFNAME ./ForestOfGrin.html REFNAME/  /REFTEXT ForestOfGrin REFTEXT/ ARTICLEREF/ . Clan Nut legendarily holds the now defunct title of Lords of the Valley of Kings, the ancient burial grounds of the later kings of Civari. This clan also has unusually close ties with the eldar as its ancestors were amongst a small group of eldar who joined the sarduni after the fall of Civari rather than return to the Fey. Legend has it that this was due to some sort of curse.

Currently Galar Nut is the Tree Lord of the Tree of Readiness at /ARTICLEREF /REFNAME ./HathIilikki.html REFNAME/  /REFTEXT Hath Iilikki REFTEXT/ ARTICLEREF/ . In this position she has a secondary responsibility to /ARTICLEREF /REFNAME ./DraelekTuroth.html REFNAME/  /REFTEXT Draelek Turoth REFTEXT/ ARTICLEREF/ , the Warden of /ARTICLEREF /REFNAME ./SuriNatha.html REFNAME/  /REFTEXT Suri Natha REFTEXT/ ARTICLEREF/ , who's clan has a small holding in the tree due to a technical responsibility for security in the northern area of the /ARTICLEREF /REFNAME ./ValeOfTears.html REFNAME/  /REFTEXT Vale of Tears REFTEXT/ ARTICLEREF/ . While Galar has no particular loyalty to Draelek she is inclined to assist him for 2 reasons. Her own claims are founded on a basis similar to those of Draelek's and she sees no reason to be at odds with Clan Turoth. Thus she is willing to help him out as long as it doesn't involve any significant cost to herself.
/SECTION Characteristics SECTION/ 

/EM Personality: EM/ Galar Nut is stubborn and obsessed with her personal mission and also quite sensitive to perceived encroachments on her prerogatives. Getting on her bad side is easy, simply hold a different opinion than she does. Getting on her good side is more difficult but she will honor obligations and return good will. She most enjoys studying history and tree lore. Those with similar interests can engage her. When she puts her mind to it she can be quite convincing and commands the loyalty of her followers.

/EM Appearance: EM/ Galar is fairly plain looking for an elf. In the field she dresses in typical elf garb and sports a medallion indicating her status as a tree lord. She also wears an ancient bracelet inscribed with eldar script and symbology of the high tree lords of ancient Civari, a relic of her family's distant past.

/EM Mannerisms: EM/ Galar is quiet amongst people she does not know but when she speaks she expects to be heard. She can be quite loud when necessary and may become bossy. She tends to use archaic mannerisms of speech and enjoys displaying a knowledge of ancient eldar and elf traditions and etiquette.

