/SECTION The Curse SECTION/ 

In fact there is a curse on the Nut clan. During the last days of Civari one of their ancestors betrayed the last king in an attempt to save the grove of Arra Kleth which once grew at the head of the Valley of Kings. The tree lord Kalash Nut, an elf, was the high grove lord of the grove of Habach Iilikki . This was one of two master groves from which the nuts of the Arra Kleth were traditionally grown. He loved an eldar woman, Milicashi, who was the sister of the last high eldar king of Civari, Falas Nathar. Nathar however would not permit them to be together.

As Civari collapsed into chaos and disorder the three kings retreated to Habach Iilikki where they made their last stand. Fearing the destruction of his grove and desiring freedom from the dictates of Falas Nathar Kalash Nut arranged to lock the king's party out of their refuge as they returned from a battle with their enemies hot on their heels. The human king Orman Tarash perished in the aftermath and when Falas Nathar confronted Kalash Nut the tree lord slew the king himself. In retribution Falas Nathar cursed Nut and all that would come from him to bare no issue. This curse was in fact so potent that it caused the grove of Habach Iilikki to whither. As the seed of every grove of Arra Kleth came ultimately from this one master grove the entire race of trees was made barren. Nathar however had no reason to curse his sister because he did not know that she bore Nut's child and thus the clan partially escaped the curse.

Kalash Nut himself however was devastated by the realization that he had sown the seeds of the destruction of the Arra Kleth. Becoming wild and suicidal he was soon killed in battle when a /ARTICLEREF /REFNAME ./ShadowFall.html REFNAME/  /REFTEXT ShadowFall REFTEXT/ ARTICLEREF/  overwhelmed Habach Iilikki. Milicashi and his son escaped to /ARTICLEREF /REFNAME ./HathIilikki.html REFNAME/  /REFTEXT Hath Iilikki REFTEXT/ ARTICLEREF/  where he took up his father's craft.

This curse is little known of even amongst the eldar. Nut himself saw to the burial of the last of the kings. The scribe Sarash Telar was one of the few who knew something of these events and when Nut found that the history he had written revealed his part in things he ordered it too sealed in Nathar's tomb. The scribe however penned another account of these last events which is one of only a very few documents which have survived to this day. The /ARTICLEREF /REFNAME ./AccountOfSarashTelar.html REFNAME/  /REFTEXT Account of Sarash Telar REFTEXT/ ARTICLEREF/  is held in the library of the /ARTICLEREF /REFNAME ./HulamicAcademyOfMagic.html REFNAME/  /REFTEXT Hulamic Academy of Magic REFTEXT/ ARTICLEREF/  in the /ARTICLEREF /REFNAME ./TownOfDinford.html REFNAME/  /REFTEXT Town of Dinford REFTEXT/ ARTICLEREF/  currently.

